The Democratic Alliance (DA) has criticised Premier David Makhura saying he's been missing from the crisis. JOHANNESBURG - There are calls for the Gauteng government to urgently intervene and address the crippling strike by employees at the province s mortuaries.The Democratic Alliance (DA) has criticised Premier David Makhura saying he's been missing from the crisis.Workers at certain government mortuaries have been on strike refusing to conduct post-mortems demanding similar benefits to pathologists.Yesterday, a Muslim family won a court order to perform an autopsy on their loved one nearly two weeks after his death, and his body released.The DA's Jack Bloom says its unacceptable that families have to go to such great lengths. It s terrible that families have to approach courts over something like this. The strike has gone on for too long and Premier Makhura needs to step in. 